Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Quarter @Roma Tomatoes{2} lengthwise. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Halve, peel, and dice @Red Onion{1}(peeled and diced) into ½-inch pieces.

Spread out tomatoes on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until soft and jammy, ~{15-20%minutes}. Meanwhile, bring 2 cups of @water{2%cups} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil in a small #pot{}.

Place half the @Bacon{3%ounce} from the package in a large, empty #pan{} over medium-high heat (use the rest as you like). Cook until bacon is crispy, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside to drain on #paper towels{}. Keep any rendered grease in pan.

Add potatoes and onion to same pan. Cook, tossing, until potatoes are crisp and onion is very soft, ~{15-20%minutes}. (TIP: Add a drizzle of oil if pan seems dry.) Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir @Spinach{5%ounce} into pan, tossing to wilt. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once water is boiling, slowly pour @Grits{1/2%cup} into pot while whisking to combine. Lower heat and reduce to a simmer. Cook until grits are thick and creamy, about ~{10%minutes}. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. TIP: If grits become stiff, add a splash of water to loosen.

Divide grits between plates and top with hash and tomatoes. Crumble bacon over top and serve.